div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 158px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Parse all Layout XML and determine if our UI Component needs to be loaded.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 98px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Found our UI Component in Layout XML

switch.text: Found our UI Component in Layout XML

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 138px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Find all <component_name>.xml configuration files that match the component name listed within the Layout XML.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 72px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Found our configuration file(s)

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 158px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Find the definition.xml file ready to be merged with our <component_name>.xml file. The merged <component_name>.xml config values take precedence over definition.xml.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 158px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: The merged configuration values are now passed to the constructor of the PHP object defined within the definition.xml. These values are then translated into JSON.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 135px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: The JSON is added to the response body as the configuration for the 'Magento_Ui/js/core/app' JS Component. This component s job is to instantiate view-models.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 199px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: 'Magento_UI/js/core/app' also requires 'Magento_UI/js/core/renderer/layout'. It calls the returned layout() function.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 148px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Merge all <component_name>.xml files together. The devdocs state that the last file merged takes precedence (but it doesn't state how to control this). Now merge with definition.xml.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 38px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: File Found

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 44px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Files merged

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; white-space: nowrap;
div.div: JSON created

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 78px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: view-model added to uiRegistry

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 210px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: 'Magento_UI/js/core/app' gets executed and requires 'Magento_UI/js/lib/knockout/bootstrap'. This module first sets Magento's custom templating engine. This engine allows KnockoutJS to use remote templates.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 59px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Custom templating engine set

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 207px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: 'Magento_UI/js/lib/knockout/bootstrap' next calls ko.applyBindings(). This function fetches all the remote templates using the custom templating engine.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 56px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Remote templates loaded

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 213px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Within the layout() function the initComponent() function instantiates the configured view-model. This view model then gets added to the uiRegistry ready to be bound to a template using the 'scope' binding.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 50px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Layout module executed

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 180px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: The view-model and view are then linked together using the applyComponents() function within the 'Magento_UI/js/lib/ko/bind/scope' module. This module provides the custom scope binding.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 59px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Response sent to client

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 66px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Standard KnockoutJS takes over
